  "text": "The Kubernetes admission webhook processing chain is structured as a hierarchical dispatcher architecture with two parallel pipelines for mutating and validating webhooks.\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n### 1. Generic Webhook Framework (pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/)\n\nThe `generic` package provides the foundational abstraction layer for webhook processing:\n\n- **interfaces.go**: Defines core abstractions:\n  - `Dispatcher` interface: The main contract for webhook dispatch with method `Dispatch(ctx context.Context, a admission.Attributes, o admission.ObjectInterfaces, hooks []webhook.WebhookAccessor) error`\n  - `Source` interface: Abstracts webhook configuration source, providing `Webhooks() []webhook.WebhookAccessor`\n  - `VersionedAttributeAccessor` interface: Handles versioning of admission attributes for different GVKs\n  - `WebhookInvocation` struct: Encapsulates invocation details (Webhook, Resource, Subresource, Kind)\n\n- **webhook.go**: Implements the generic `Webhook` struct that orchestrates the admission flow:\n  - `NewWebhook()`: Factory function that creates a Webhook with a source factory and dispatcher factory\n  - `Dispatch()` method: Entry point that retrieves webhooks from the source and delegates to the dispatcher\n  - `ShouldCallHook()` method: Determines if a webhook should be invoked by checking namespace selector, object selector, rules matching, and CEL match conditions\n\n### 2. WebhookAccessor Abstraction Layer (webhook/accessors.go)\n\nThe `WebhookAccessor` interface provides a unified abstraction over both mutating and validating webhooks (which have slightly different fields):\n\n- Implements methods to access webhook metadata: GetName(), GetUID(), GetRules(), GetFailurePolicy(), GetTimeoutSeconds(), GetClientConfig(), etc.\n- Two concrete implementations:\n  - `mutatingWebhookAccessor`: Wraps `v1.MutatingWebhook` with UID and configuration name\n  - `validatingWebhookAccessor`: Wraps `v1.ValidatingWebhook` with UID and configuration name\n- Uses sync.Once for lazy initialization of selectors and REST clients\n\n### 3. Configuration Management Layer\n\nTwo configuration managers manage webhook configuration objects and create webhook accessors:\n\n- **mutating_webhook_manager.go**: \n  - `mutatingWebhookConfigurationManager` implements `generic.Source`\n  - `NewMutatingWebhookConfigurationManager()`: Creates manager from SharedInformerFactory\n  - Caches webhook accessors by configuration name for efficiency\n  - `Webhooks()` method returns sorted list of `WebhookAccessor` objects\n\n- **validating_webhook_manager.go**:\n  - `validatingWebhookConfigurationManager` implements `generic.Source`\n  - `NewValidatingWebhookConfigurationManager()`: Creates manager from SharedInformerFactory\n  - Similar caching and sorting strategy as mutating manager\n  - Maintains informer event handlers for dynamic updates\n\n### 4. Mutating Webhook Dispatcher with Reinvocation Logic\n\nThe mutating webhook pipeline (**webhook/mutating/dispatcher.go**) implements sophisticated reinvocation logic:\n\n- **mutatingDispatcher struct**: Implements `generic.Dispatcher` interface\n- **Dispatch() method**: \n  - Retrieves or initializes `webhookReinvokeContext` from the reinvocation context\n  - Tracks which webhooks have been previously invoked using reinvocation policy\n  - For each webhook, calls `ShouldCallHook()` to determine if it matches\n  - Checks if object has changed (from other admission plugins) to trigger reinvocation\n  - Skips webhooks with `NeverReinvocationPolicy` during reinvocation\n  - Calls `callAttrMutatingHook()` which patches the object\n  - Records patches in audit annotations with `PatchAuditAnnotationPrefix`\n  - If webhook patches the object, sets `ShouldReinvoke()` flag to reinvoke earlier eligible plugins\n  - Webhooks with `IfNeededReinvocationPolicy` are registered for potential reinvocation\n\n- **webhookReinvokeContext**: Tracks invocation state across reinvocation rounds:\n  - `ShouldReinvokeWebhook(uid)`: Checks if webhook should be called in reinvocation\n  - `RequireReinvokingPreviouslyInvokedPlugins()`: Marks that reinvocation is needed\n  - `AddReinvocableWebhookToPreviouslyInvoked()`: Records webhooks that support reinvocation\n\n### 5. Validating Webhook Dispatcher with Parallel Dispatch\n\nThe validating webhook pipeline (**webhook/validating/dispatcher.go**) implements parallel execution:\n\n- **validatingDispatcher struct**: Implements `generic.Dispatcher` interface\n- **Dispatch() method**:\n  - First collects all relevant hooks by calling `ShouldCallHook()` for each webhook\n  - Pre-compiles versioned attributes for all required GVKs to avoid redundant conversions\n  - **Parallel execution**: Uses `sync.WaitGroup` and goroutines to call hooks concurrently\n  - Each goroutine calls `callHook()` with its own invocation and versioned attribute\n  - Collects errors in an error channel with capacity for panic recovery (2x hooks)\n  - Implements panic recovery with `utilruntime.HandleCrash()` to prevent one webhook panic from crashing the API server\n  - Handles failure policies (Ignore vs Fail) for each webhook independently\n  - Records metrics for each webhook (success, latency, rejection reason)\n  - Returns first error encountered, or nil if all validations pass\n\n### 6. Plugin Layer\n\nTwo plugin implementations bridge the admission system with the webhook framework:\n\n- **mutating/plugin.go**:\n  - `Plugin` wraps `generic.Webhook`\n  - Implements `admission.MutationInterface`\n  - `NewMutatingWebhook()`: Creates plugin with `NewMutatingWebhookConfigurationManager` as source\n  - Uses `newMutatingDispatcher()` factory for the mutating dispatcher\n  - `Admit()` method calls `Webhook.Dispatch()`\n\n- **validating/plugin.go**:\n  - `Plugin` wraps `generic.Webhook`\n  - Implements `admission.ValidationInterface`\n  - `NewValidatingAdmissionWebhook()`: Creates plugin with `NewValidatingWebhookConfigurationManager` as source\n  - Uses `newValidatingDispatcher()` factory for the validating dispatcher\n  - `Validate()` method calls `Webhook.Dispatch()`\n\n### 7. API Type Definitions\n\nThe API layer defines the webhook configuration resources:\n\n- **admissionregistration/v1/types.go** (current stable version):\n  - `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` struct: Cluster-scoped resource containing list of `MutatingWebhook` objects\n  - `ValidatingWebhookConfiguration` struct: Cluster-scoped resource containing list of `ValidatingWebhook` objects\n  - `MutatingWebhook` fields: Name, ClientConfig, Rules, FailurePolicy, MatchPolicy, NamespaceSelector, ObjectSelector, SideEffects, TimeoutSeconds, AdmissionReviewVersions, ReinvocationPolicy, MatchConditions\n  - `ValidatingWebhook` fields: Same as MutatingWebhook\n  - `ReinvocationPolicyType`: Enum with \"Never\" and \"IfNeeded\" values (only in MutatingWebhook)\n\n- **admissionregistration/v1beta1/types.go** (deprecated in v1.16, removed in v1.22):\n  - Same structure as v1 but marked as deprecated\n  - `MutatingWebhookConfiguration` and `ValidatingWebhookConfiguration` with identical fields\n\n## Processing Chain Flow\n\n1. **Admission Request**: API server invokes `Plugin.Admit()` (mutating) or `Plugin.Validate()` (validating)\n2. **Generic Dispatch**: Calls `Webhook.Dispatch()` in generic/webhook.go\n3. **Configuration Retrieval**: Gets webhooks from manager's `Source.Webhooks()` which lists current configurations\n4. **Concrete Dispatcher**: Calls `dispatcher.Dispatch()` with webhook accessors\n5. **Mutating Path**: \n   - Handles reinvocation context\n   - Iterates webhooks sequentially\n   - Patches object for each webhook\n   - Tracks changes to trigger reinvocation\n6. **Validating Path**:\n   - Pre-processes all webhooks\n   - Spawns parallel goroutines for concurrent validation\n   - Collects results with error channel\n7. **Response**: Returns nil on success or aggregated error\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n- **Strategy Pattern**: `Dispatcher` interface allows different dispatch strategies (mutating vs validating)\n- **Adapter Pattern**: `WebhookAccessor` unifies v1.MutatingWebhook and v1.ValidatingWebhook APIs\n- **Observer Pattern**: Configuration managers use informers for dynamic webhook updates\n- **Factory Pattern**: Dispatcher factories inject concrete dispatcher implementations\n- **Lazy Evaluation**: Configuration managers use lazy caching to avoid redundant CEL compilation\n- **Reinvocation Pattern**: Mutating webhooks can request reinvocation if previous plugins modified the object\n- **Parallel Execution**: Validating webhooks use goroutines for concurrent execution\n"
}

